      "content": "The concept of \"natural rights\" is a cornerstone of libertarian philosophy, and it's particularly relevant to the issue of internet regulation. The idea that individuals possess inherent, God-given rights to life, liberty, and property (including free speech) is a fundamental tenet of libertarian thought. If the internet is seen as an extension of the human mind and a means of self-expression, then any government regulation that restricts or controls online speech can be viewed as a direct assault on the individual's right to self-defense and self-expression. This is in line with the 18th-century philosopher Thomas Paine's argument that the right to free speech is a natural right, unalienable and universal.",
